# CcShell Wiki

CcShell-runtime is a CraftOS-PC addon layer that turns the shell into a more structured, package-driven environment.

It is not a full operating system in the traditional sense. The base is still CraftOS-PC. This project adds:

- a `sys` bridge for Lua-to-Python communication
- host-side file operations
- Windows taskbar control
- package installation and dependency handling
- optional ROM program trees for different computer types

## Quick links

- [sys API](Sys-API)
- [BridgeFS](BridgeFS)
- [How to make a package](How-To-Make-A-Package)

## Main concepts

- `base` installs the runtime layout
- `sys` exposes the Lua bridge API
- `bridgefs` adds host filesystem support and the `file` debug command
- `python` is a special pacman target that refreshes the host Python scripts

## Installing

The normal install flow is:

```text
pacman -S base
```

Optional program trees can be forced during base install:

```text
pacman -S base --advanced --fun --http
```

